Adult students, especially working professionals upgrading their skills, need to be able to progress through basic courses in such a manner as to benefit from their real-life experience. Such courses as computer literacy and microcomputer applications for non-computer science majors and introduction to Pascal programming for computer science majors would seem to fall into this categoty. The present tutorial explores the implementation of such a self-paced course structure as it has been used in our graduate program in applied computer science,